Add base_kwargs to client and refactor error handling
The LsRestClientTestClient now includes base_kwargs as part of keyword arguments. This allows additional parameters to be passed with each request. Error handling has also been enhanced in the exceptions module, allowing it to handle cases where no specific exceptions are provided. This raises errors more effectively depending on the particular situation.

Add support for PDF content in LsRestClientResponse
The update extends the LsRestClientResponse class to handle 'application/pdf' content. If the response content type is 'application/pdf', the content is now directly assigned instead of being decoded. Also incremented the package version in pyproject.toml from 2.0.0 to 2.1.0.
changed version back from 2.0.1 to 1.7.0 because of the gorilla/banana problem

Add __repr__ method to LsRestClient
Implemented a __repr__ method to provide a clear string representation of the LsRestClient instance, including its name and base_url. Updated the project version in pyproject.toml to 1.7.1 to reflect this addition.

Refactor request handling and update tests
Refactor the request handling to separate real_request method for clarity. Update test base URL to https://httpbin.org/ and adjust test case accordingly. Bump version to 1.7.2 in pyproject.toml.

Add LsFastApiClientBase abstraction for FastAPI clients
Introduced an abstract base class, `LsFastApiClientBase`, to streamline FastAPI client implementation. It provides methods for client registration, health checks, and enforces base URL definition via an abstract method.

Replace custom `cache_control` decorator with `fastapi_lsoft.cache_control`
Removed the manually implemented `cache_control` decorator in favor of the external `fastapi_lsoft.cache_control` to streamline the code and reduce redundancy. Adjusted imports accordingly.

Replace custom `cache_control` decorator with `fastapi_lsoft.cache_control`

Introduce request caching support and refactor test clients
Added caching support to LsRestClient with configurable backends (SQLite and Redis). Refactored test fixtures by introducing `clients.py` with separate cached and non-cached clients. Updated tests to utilize cached clients where applicable and ensured compatibility.

Add Redis caching support and enhance LsRestClient configurations
Introduced Redis as a caching backend for `LsRestClient` with configurable settings. Updated `docker-compose.yml` to include a Redis service. Enhanced `LsRestClient` with `pydantic-settings` support for managing configurations. Added new test cases for caching scenarios and adjusted dependencies in `pyproject.toml`.
Bump version to 3.3.0 and add `redis` extra for optional dependency management

Replace echo service in `docker-compose.yml` and enhance middleware, caching, and tests
Removed the `echo` service from `docker-compose.yml` and updated FastAPI application with `FastapiLsoftMiddleware`. Refined caching logic using `fastapi_lsoft` dependencies and introduced `etag` support. Enhanced test coverage and updated tests to reflect caching, ETag logic, and expiration policies. Updated dependencies in `pyproject.toml` and `poetry.lock`.
Bump version to 3.3.2 in `pyproject.toml` to prepare for release

Enhance `/product` endpoint, caching, and ETag logic; update dependencies and tests
Refined the `/product` endpoint with improved caching and ETag generation using `fastapi_lsoft`. Introduced `stale-while-revalidate` support in `LsRestClient` and enhanced caching configurations. Updated dependencies and added `pytest-asyncio` for asynchronous test execution. Improved test suite for caching, ETag validation, and performance tracking.
